description: Peeled and grated zucchini blends perfectly into these brownies, no one will suspect they are veggie packed.
name: Zucchini Brownies Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Pre-heat the oven to 170°C/150°C fan-forced and line a square baking tin with parchment paper. Place the grated zucchini in a colander to drain.
Whisk the egg, oil, maple syrup and vanilla together in a large bowl. Sift in cocoa powder, baking soda and salt and whisk to combine.
Squeeze excess moisture out of the zucchini, pat dry with paper towels and stir in to the brownie batter, followed by the flour. Mix well to combine.
Pour into the baking dish and bake for 25 minutes, until still a little gooey in the centre when tested with a skewer. Leave to cool for 1 hour before slicing and serving.
